The paper deals with the estimation of mutual information between two random variables, which is a topic that falls under information theory (cs.IT). The use of kernel density-based plug-in estimators and the proposed ensemble estimator suggest that the paper may also be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions variable selection in classification, which is a topic in data science (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses cases where one or both random variables may be discrete or continuous, which suggests that it may be relevant to statistical inference (cs.SI).
